==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teuton
<hw>Teu"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Teutons</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Teutones</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>Teutones</ets>, <ets>Teutoni</ets>,
the name of a Germanic people, probably akin to E. <ets>Dutch</ets>. Cf.
<er>Dutch</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of an ancient German tribe;
later, a name applied to any member of the Germanic race in Europe; now
used to designate a German, Dutchman, Scandinavian, etc., in distinction
from a Celt or one of a Latin race.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of the Teutonic branch of the
Indo-European, or Aryan, family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teutonic</ent>⟦br⟧
